  "text": "WebIDL to C++ Binding Discovery for Fetch API\n\nThis mapping documents the correspondence between WebIDL interface definitions and their C++ implementations in the Firefox codebase for the Fetch API.\n\n**Request Interface:**\n- WebIDL: dom/webidl/Request.webidl - Defines the JavaScript-facing Request interface with properties like method, url, headers, mode, credentials, cache, redirect, etc.\n- C++ Header: dom/fetch/Request.h - Contains the Request class that inherits from FetchBody<Request> and nsWrapperCache, implementing the WebIDL interface\n- C++ Implementation: dom/fetch/Request.cpp - Provides the implementation of Request methods and constructor\n\n**Response Interface:**\n- WebIDL: dom/webidl/Response.webidl - Defines the JavaScript-facing Response interface with properties like type, url, status, statusText, headers, etc.\n- C++ Header: dom/fetch/Response.h - Contains the Response class that inherits from FetchBody<Response> and nsWrapperCache, implementing the WebIDL interface\n- C++ Implementation: dom/fetch/Response.cpp - Provides the implementation of Response methods including static constructors (error, redirect, json)\n\n**Headers Interface:**\n- WebIDL: dom/webidl/Headers.webidl - Defines the JavaScript-facing Headers interface with methods like append, delete, get, has, set, and iterable support\n- C++ Header: dom/fetch/Headers.h - Contains the Headers class that wraps InternalHeaders and is used by Request and Response objects\n- C++ Implementation: dom/fetch/Headers.cpp - Provides the implementation of Headers methods for manipulating HTTP headers\n\n**FetchEvent Interface:**\n- WebIDL: dom/webidl/FetchEvent.webidl - Defines the FetchEvent interface exposed to ServiceWorkers, extending ExtendableEvent with request, preloadResponse, clientId, resultingClientId, handled properties and respondWith() method\n- C++ Header: dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.h - Contains the FetchEvent class (lines 132-195) that extends ExtendableEvent\n- C++ Implementation: dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.cpp - Provides the implementation of FetchEvent methods including PostInit, RespondWith, and PreventDefault\n\nAll interfaces are defined following the WHATWG Fetch specification and are exposed to both Window and Worker contexts (except FetchEvent which is ServiceWorker-specific)."
}

